+| SEC-003 | High | `partners/partner_profile.py`, `partners/partner_accounts_and_transactions.py` | Legacy partner profile and wallet routes remain `AllowAny` while resolving principals directly from `partner_session_token`, making profile, banking, and withdrawal surfaces depend on raw token possession rather than explicit authenticated principals. | open | Source inspection during security-audit Phase 0 |
+| SEC-004 | Medium | `huz/settings.py`, `huz/urls.py`, `common/utility.py`, `booking/models.py`, `partners/models.py` | Uploaded passport, payment, complaint, and partner-company documents are stored in local media and can become anonymously reachable if `SERVE_MEDIA_AND_STATIC_FROM_DJANGO` is enabled; confirm production flag discipline and media exposure controls. | open | Source inspection during security-audit Phase 0 |
